        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Answering question at Step t+1 correctly",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "3006 ASSISTments 2009 learners, 22397 ASSISTments 2012 learners, 1000 Juniy learners",
          "ASSISTments, Junyi",
          "Sequence of Answers, LMS logs",
          "[Sequences of Answers, Spped, Attempts, Hints]",
          "Previous models tend to look at KT as sequences of answers, leaving behind the different types of learner behavior that are relevant to model a learner’s knowledge state.",
          "LBKT has 2 modules: \n\nDifferentiated Behavior Effect Quantifying: it looks at 3 specific learning behaviors (Speed, Attempts and Hints). \n\nFused Behavior Effect Measuring (FBEM): Behaviors are not independent from one another. For that reason, the authors use a separate module to measure dependencies between behavioral features. ",
          "Learners are represented as matrix that is updated with more and more exercises. The update of knowledge states includes a forget gate and a knowledge acquisition vector. ",
          "DKT, DKT_concat, AT-DKT, DFVMN, DDMKT, SAKT, AKT, LPKT, LBKT-DB, LBKT-FB, LBKT-Forget",
          "Holdout Method",
          "AST09\n{RMSE: 0.4203 - LBKT, AUC: 0.7863 - LBKT, Accuracy: 0.7380 - LBKT}\n\nAST12\n{RMSE: 0.4043 - LBKT, AUC: 0.7823 - LBKT, Accuracy: 0.7613 - LBKT}\n\nJunyi\n{RMSE: 0.3494 - LBKT, AUC: 0.7723 - LBKT, Accuracy: 0.8362 - LBKT}",
          "Authors create a new methodd that looks to introduce Learner Behavior. Model is validated on 3 public datasets. Multiple Ablation Studies are also performed to measure sensitiviy of the model to different parameters.",
          "No Cross-Validation,\n\nLimited number of learner behaviors considered in approach.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
